N:backend-testing
D:Write backend test plans and implementations for business logic, APIs, database-backed flows, and authentication paths across Node.js or Python services. Use when the user needs unit tests, integration tests, auth tests, coverage hardening, or flaky backend test fixes.
G:backend-testing testing unit-tests integration-tests api-tests auth-tests pytest jest supertest coverage flaky-backend-test
U[6]:
  Developing or refactoring backend logic that needs regression coverage
  Adding REST, GraphQL, queue, or database-backed endpoints
  Verifying authentication, authorization, validation, and side effects
  Fixing flaky backend suites caused by shared state or open handles
  Choosing the right test layer before writing implementation
  Hardening coverage before broader prompt or workflow optimization
S[7]{n,action,details}:
  1,Triage test surface,Capture runtime, framework, runner, dependencies, auth model, and exact behavior to prove
  2,Choose layer,Pick unit vs integration vs auth vs regression at the cheapest layer that still proves the contract
  3,Isolate environment,Use separate test config, resettable DB state, and mocked external boundaries
  4,Write high-leverage cases,Prioritize business-critical, auth, validation, side-effect, and known bug paths
  5,Keep assertions observable,Assert status codes, payload shape, DB state, events, and permission boundaries
  6,Use support files,Load references/framework-recipes.md or references/troubleshooting.md for boilerplate and debugging detail
  7,Return structured outcome,Report test surface, plan, implementation, run commands, and remaining gaps
R[6]:
  Start with the smallest test that proves the user-visible contract
  Treat auth and validation failures as first-class scenarios
  Prefer deterministic setup over shared mutable fixtures
  Flaky tests are correctness bugs, not CI noise
  Add eval coverage before starting any skill-autoresearch loop on this skill
  Keep framework-specific boilerplate in references so the main skill stays reviewable
E[4]{desc,in,out}:
  "Auth coverage for a Node API","Add backend tests for the login and refresh-token endpoints in this Express API.","Chooses isolated API/auth tests; covers success and failure cases; verifies token or session side effects"
  "FastAPI validation regression","Our FastAPI order endpoint accepts negative quantities. Add tests before the fix.","Locks the bug at the HTTP boundary with pytest/TestClient-style coverage"
  "Flaky Jest suite","These Jest API tests pass alone but fail when the full suite runs. What should I do?","Investigates shared state, leaked handles, timer cleanup, and deterministic resets before widening coverage"
  "Layer selection","Should this repository method get a unit test or an integration test?","Chooses the fastest layer that still proves the important behavior"
